KnowledgeBase.Title: Example Boolean compareGE 009
KnowledgeBase.RelatedFunctions: compare compareEQ compareNE compareGT compareLT compareLE

Example.Description: These examples use the compareGE function to determine whether the first object has a greater value or is equal to the value of the second object. The compareGE function returns the Boolean value, true or false.

Syntax.Note: The Boolean value false has a state value of 1.
The result from the &#62 operation is also the value 1.
